HEADWORD: Waterlandian
<hw>Wa`ter*land"i*an</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of
a body of Dutch Anabaptists who separated from the Mennonites in the
sixteenth century; -- so called from a district in North Holland
denominated <ets>Waterland</ets>.</def>⟦br⟧
